item.title: CVE-2018-5529|2024-09-16T18:55:42.284Z -- f5%20networks%2C%20inc. -- big-ip%20apm%20client%20for%20linux%20and%20mac%20osx
item.description: The svpn component of the F5 BIG-IP APM client prior to version 7.1.7 for Linux and Mac OS X runs as a privileged process and can allow an unprivileged user to assume super-user privileges on the local client host. A malicious local unprivileged user may gain knowledge of sensitive information, manipulate certain data, or disrupt service.
